for i_dataset, ((X, y), algo_params) in enumerate(datasets):
    # update parameters with dataset-specific values
    params = default_base.copy()
    params.update(algo_params)
    if i_dataset == 2:
        break

algorithm = dbscan

    y_pred = algorithm.labels_.astype(np.int)

    y_pred = algorithm.predict(X)

In [103]:
from sklearn import cluster, mixture
from itertools import cycle, islice

for i_dataset, ((X, y), algo_params) in enumerate(datasets):
    # update parameters with dataset-specific values
    params = default_base.copy()
    params.update(algo_params)
    if i_dataset == 3:
        break

dbscan = cluster.DBSCAN(eps=0.35)
#two_means = cluster.MiniBatchKMeans(n_clusters=2)
three_means = cluster.MiniBatchKMeans(n_clusters=3)
gmm = mixture.GaussianMixture(
        n_components=params['n_clusters'], covariance_type='full')

for algorithm in [dbscan, three_means, gmm]:

    algorithm.fit(X)
    if hasattr(algorithm, 'labels_'):
        y_pred = algorithm.labels_.astype(np.int)
    else:
        y_pred = algorithm.predict(X)

    colors = np.array(list(islice(cycle(['#377eb8', '#ff7f00', '#4daf4a',
                                         '#f781bf', '#a65628', '#984ea3',
                                         '#999999', '#e41a1c', '#dede00']),
                                  int(max(y_pred) + 1))))

    # add black color for outliers (if any)
    colors = np.append(colors, ["#000000"])
    plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], s=10, color=colors[y_pred])
    plt.title(algorithm.__class__.__name__)
    plt.show()
